    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-25T02:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-25T02:35:00-05:00" n="587"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9111/651: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-25T11:00:00+03:25"
                            >May 25, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 25—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Legation’s 50, May 21, 8 p.m.<note n="14" xml:id="d587fn14">Not
                        printed.</note> I have just had my first interview with the new Minister of
                    Foreign Affairs<note n="15" xml:id="d587fn15">Ali Soheily.</note> whom I had met
                    several times in London last Spring.</p>
                <p>He could not have been more cordial and began the conversation by stating at once
                    that “we simply must do something to normalize our official relations. I believe
                    I understand the position of the American Government better than most Persians
                    and you may count on my helping in every possible way.”</p>
                <p>Later I referred to the article in <hi rend="italic">Times</hi> of April 25th and
                    he said he knew we had no control over our press “less even than the British
                    have over theirs.”</p>
                <p>He did not mention the Amiranian Oil Company<note n="16" xml:id="d587fn16">See
                            <ref target="#pg_752">pp. 752</ref> ff.</note> and neither did I.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
